-- Premier League Club Fulham Signs Uniform Contract With Adidas
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-05-17T11:01:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-17/premier-league-club-fulham-signs-uniform-contract-with-adidas.html
Fulham signed a “long-term”
agreement to have  Adidas AG (ADS)  supply the English Premier League
soccer club’s uniforms and apparel.  The west London team didn’t disclose details of the deal in
a statement on the its  website . BasicNet SpA’s Kappa brand has
been the Cottagers’ kit supplier.  “Adidas has a fantastic football heritage and tradition
and I know that we will work well together,” Fulham Chief
Executive Officer Alistair Mackintosh said.  Fulham, which is 15th in the 20-team Premier League, closes
its season at Swansea in two days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 